  +1 -0		trunk/modules/chanserv/set.c (File Modified) 
  +4 -1		trunk/src/node.c (File Modified) 


jilles      2006/08/07 14:06:59 UTC	(20060807-6017)
  Log:
  Add support for CIDR channel bans/exceptions and akills.
  src/cidr.c provides match_ips() for matching a CIDR mask
  against an IP address and match_cidr() for channel bans
  (with nick!user@). In accordance with match(), zero is
  returned for a match, non-zero otherwise. The code is
  mostly taken from ratbox but modified to eliminate OS
  dependency for IPv6.
  CIDR is checked whether the ircd supports it or not.
  ChanServ RECOVER used to only check host and vhost matches
  for the implied unban but now also checks ip match and
  CIDR.
  

  Changes:	Modified:
  +3 -1		trunk/README (File Modified) 
