jilles      2006/07/29 19:49:23 UTC	(20060729-5967)
  Log:
  Store the channelTS of registered channels in the
  private:channelts metadata entry. If the entry does
  not exist, the channel registration time is used.
  This is used for:
  1. forcing TS back to deop people recreating
     channels, if chanserv::changets is enabled
  2. not restoring topics if keeptopic is enabled
     but topiclock is not
  

  Changes:	Modified:
  +26 -23	trunk/modules/chanserv/main.c (File Modified) 
  +15 -1	trunk/src/services.c (File Modified) 


jilles      2006/07/29 19:42:29 UTC	(20060729-5965)
  Log:
  handle_topic_from(): if our uplink is bursting and trying
  to change the topic on a channel that already has a topic,
  assume our topic won and ignore the change. This stops
  some redundant topic changes if topiclock is enabled,
  which are visible with some ircds such as inspircd.
  

  Changes:	Modified:
  +6 -0		trunk/src/ptasks.c (File Modified) 


