jilles      2006/07/10 17:50:42 UTC	(20060710-5848)
  Log:
  Make sure not to QUIT chansvs.nick if chansvs.nick is NULL.
  

  Changes:	Modified:
  +6 -3		trunk/src/signal.c (File Modified) 


jilles      2006/07/10 16:01:44 UTC	(20060710-5846)
  Log:
  Postpone actual signal handling to the end of the main loop,
  functions like stdio, malloc, expire_check, db_save are
  not safe from signals. The signal handler just sets a
  variable.
  Exception is SIGUSR1 (out of memory) as we cannot safely
  return from there. So there we try (in a hackish way) to
  notify the network and log files (using write(2)) and
  abort(3) the process.
  

  Changes:	Modified:
  +1 -0		trunk/include/extern.h (File Modified) 
  +3 -0		trunk/src/send.c (File Modified) 
  +47 -11	trunk/src/signal.c (File Modified) 


jilles      2006/07/10 13:18:50 UTC	(20060710-5838)
